I started using the name 10 years ago when it was first released when I was 10yrs old... at the time I was a hardcore computer gamer.  4 years ago I made friends with someone who enjoyed the outside world and started having more fun outside. HD..  Highdrifter.  Two reasons.  First:  There's a technique in fly fishing called high stick nymphing.  In a suitable run or pool, the technique is to drift your fly without an indicator, leaving your rod up and out at arm's length.  You feel the takes better because there's less slack line (no need to mend) and you're better connected to your fly!!  Hence the word, highdrifting.  The second is PG 13...  I'm a born wanderer, and it's usually the high road I take..  cheers!  H to the D
